			<td><br>Ryan Block is the editor-in-chief of Engadget, a web magazine covering consumer electronics and technology. In addition to appearing to speak at Engadget events and co-hosting a weekly podcast, he is also a contributor and a founding editor of Joystiq, and a technology critic and commentator who has written for Business 2.0, and appeared on G4’s Attack of the Show. Ryan has been quoted in Business Week, The New York Times, The Guardian, and The Wall St. Journal, and was named one of Paper Magazine’s Beautiful People, 2006. Prior to Engadget, he worked in network engineering before returning to his education in writing and philosophy at the New School University in New York. He currently resides in San Francisco, California.</td>
